  <static seed="95" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionAdditionWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>Selena and Anthony are sharing a pizza. Selena ate <m>{{\frac{1}{8}}}</m> of the pizza, and Anthony ate <m>{{\frac{2}{7}}}</m> of the pizza. How much of the pizza was eaten in total?</p>
<p>They ate <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of the pizza.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{23}{56}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is an addition problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{8}}} + {{\frac{2}{7}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 7}{8 \cdot 7}+\frac{2 \cdot 8}{7 \cdot 8} \\
      \amp = \frac{7}{56} + \frac{16}{56} \\
      \amp = \frac{7+16}{56} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{23}{56}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>They ate <m>{{\frac{23}{56}}}</m> of the pizza.</p>
</solution>
